%S A396911 0,1,4,9,17,30,43,64,85,106,127,161,195,229,263,297,331,386,441,496,
%T A396911 551,606,661,716,771,826,881,970,1059,1148,1237,1326,1415,1504,1593,
%U A396911 1682,1771,1860,1949,2038,2127,2216,2305,2449,2593,2737,2881,3025,3169,3313,3457
%N A396911 Shortest path indices during walk over golden ratio phyllotaxis starting at the center.
%C A396911 Start with spiral lattice generated by (k^d * cos(k*theta), k^d * sin(k*theta)) for theta being the golden angle (A131988), d = 1/2 and k = 0, 1, 2, 3, ... . This set of points is also known as Vogel's phyllotaxis model.
%C A396911 Next, starting at point (0,0), move to closest unvisited point. a(n) is the index k corresponding to the point reached after n moves.
%C A396911 From _Pontus von Brömssen_, Jun 10 2026: (Start)
%C A396911 Can ties occur between multiple closest candidate points?
%C A396911 Is the sequence increasing or could an inward step occur?
%C A396911 Are the first differences (1, 3, 5, 8, 13, 13, 21, 21, 21, 21, ...) always Fibonacci numbers (A000045)?
%C A396911 What can be said about the run lengths (1, 1, 1, 1, 2, 4, 6, 10, 16, 25, ...) of the first differences?
%C A396911 (End)
%C A396911 No reduction on index in the first 1000 terms. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jun 21 2026
%H A396911 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A396911/b396911.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..999</a>
%H A396911 Pontus von Brömssen, <a href="/A396911/a396911.png">Illustration for n=0..27</a>.
%F A396911 Conjecture: a(n) <= (3/2) * n^2. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jun 21 2026
%e A396911 Below is table of Cartesian coordinates of the first 10 points:
