%e A396911 We start at point (0.00, 0.00) that corresponds to k = 0, therefore a(0) = 0.
%e A396911 Unvisited point closest to (0.00, 0.00) is (-0.74, 0.68) corresponding to k = 1, therefore a(1) = 1.
%e A396911 Unvisited point closest to (-0.74, 0.68) is (-1.97, -0.35) corresponding to k = 4, therefore a(2) = 4.
%e A396911 Unvisited point closest to (-1.97, -0.35) is (-2.77, 1.14) corresponding to k = 9, therefore a(3) = 9.
